      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted across four refinement levels (coarse: 42k elements; medium: 118k; fine: 312k; extra-fine: 780k) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for peak von Mises stress in proximal femur is 1.4%, well below the 5% acceptance threshold. Production mesh (312k C3D10 tetrahedral elements) selected. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
