      "rationale": "Twelve paired cadaveric femora (6 donors, bilateral) used for primary validation. Specimens span age range 58–74 years, BMD T-score range −1.2 to +0.8, and BMI range 22–31 kg/m². Sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 8% BMD change difference. Donor demographics documented in IRB-approved protocol. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
